729640f-a.folder: Seguine Avenue & Wilbur Street, Staten Island, NY
729640f-a.text:
(1)
Seguine Avenue, west side, between Wilbur Street and Melville Street, showing the Seguine House, a colonial home. It appears on the James Bulter map of 1853 as having belonged to the Seguine family; the Beers's map of 1874 shows it to have belonged to J. Middleton, and was known as the Prince's Bay House; the 1907 and 1917 maps of G. W. Bromley indicate it as the Chas. S.T. Stout house.
1924.
P. L. Sperr
(2)
A distant view of the house in an easterly direction, as seen from
the west bank of Lemon Creek.
May 14, 1932.
P. L. Sperr
(3)
The same, an additional view.
